<br>
Before you jump on your anti-american soapbox next time please do us all a favor and give us something worthwhile to think on.<br>
<br>
I have done extensive searching and am convinced that there are no treaties, accords, protocols or agreements in place between the United States and any other country or political body that have established airport lounges as &quot;international territory&quot;.<br>
<br>
From the beginning this did not sound right.  If you get in a fight in an airport bar you go to a local jail, not to a federal holding facility.  Even Maritime law tells you that, at a minimum, once you are within 12 miles of a country's coastline you are subjuct to their laws for the duration of your time within that 12-mile boundary.<br>
<br>
Why on earth would Maritime law establish a 12-mile law-inclusive boundary yet inland airports have a mysterious pocket somewhere in a terminal that fell under &quot;international law&quot;?<br>
<br>
Of interest: Even the embassies we host in our country are not ever considered to be sovereign soil of the hosted country.  Some staff individuals (i.e. Ambassador, Consular, etc.) are sometimes granted Diplomatic Immunity but that is for their person and possessions only - not the facilities they occupy.  It is well known that while we customarily make no overt attempts to interfere with any embassy's operations we have no qualms about tapping their phone lines, net connections, etc.  C'est la vie.  So, an Ambassador to the United States from a friendly, allied, NATO-member country doesn't even have a &quot;get out of jail free card&quot; inside his/her embassy but anyone drinking Zima in an airport bar does? ROFL<br>
<br>
By the way, there is no specific &quot;international law&quot; body... no court, no legislature, no enforcers.  There is a &quot;World Court&quot; but it is not recognized by the United States, and as far as I can tell Canada never signed on either.  Even that court is more of a self-described &quot;mediation&quot; service that cannot and will not hand out actual judgements.<br>
<br>
&quot;International Law&quot; refers to treaties, pacts, accords, etc. that have been signed by two or more sovereign parties, and only those parties involved as signers of those deals are subject to them.<br>
<br>
I wholeheartedly doubt that the U.S. ever signed any such agreement that would toss away our control over our own airport facilities, and if we had (which I can find no evidence of) then even under the accepted tenets of establishing/de-establishing international law our &quot;Patriot Act&quot; (signed early this year) or our upcoming &quot;Homeland Security Act&quot; would supercede it and render moot any previous agreements.<br>
<br>
This whole idea you've brought up - even the title of this thread - is leftist bullshit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ueyrit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyrit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/20/02 12:45:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1722.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Airport Lounges are local jurisdiction</span><hr size=1> On another note the whole registering and fingerprinting of muslims at border visiting the US is fucked up. I mean why dont they register and finger print the jews or them crazy irish fucks? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uslassh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slassh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 311<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/20/02 1:14:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1722.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> er...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;If you think using a plane of innocent people to blow up buildings full of other innocent people is definable as &quot;right&quot;...<br>
